clearest water seen in past 15+ years- slight chop

Unusually clear water appearance; high sun angle; slight wave action; high scattered cloud cover; air temp in mid 70's.
See comments from Storet site at north end of lake (#663150) on this date.
Same information/comments as entered for site at north end of Balsam Lake.
Air temperature in mid-80's- less than 5% cloud cover- slight wave action with wind from west/southwest- 5-8 knots.

Partly cloudy- slight wave action- temperature in low 80's.  Eagle nesting activity on east shore of Balsam Lake- as earlier reported; two young Bald Eagles- both females- approximately 10 weeks old- left the next during previous week.  There are approximately seven (7) Bald Eagles frequenting the shoreline areas of the lake.
No wind- calm water surface- air temp at 84 degrees- 50% cloud cover. Same comments as stated for other site this date.
70% overcast sky- light breeze- calm water.  Air temp at 74 degrees.

High- cirrus clouds- good sun angle-light breeze from northwest- light wave action- air temperature 80 degrees- water temp at 3 feet below surface at 74 degrees.  Water clarity continues to remain at excellent levels throughout the summer months.

Mostly clear sky with good sun angle- air temp about 75 degrees with very little wind and relatively calm water.  Water clarity has deminished nearly 30% from readings taken about 17 days ago.  Rainfall amounts of nearly 4 inches during the week may have contributed to more than normal runoff into area lakes from surrounding wathershed.
High- thin- scattered clouds.  10 knot breeze from the south with light wave action.  Sun angle at approx 45 degrees.
Cloudless sky with air temp approx 75 degrees.  Nearly calm water surface.  This will be my final submission of water quality monitoring data for 2007
Same data as entered for site at north end of Balsam Lake on this date.

Lake clarity continues to be exceptionally poor- especially compared to readings same time last year.  For today's readings: light breeze with nearly calm water surface.  Temperature in mid-70's.  Light wispy clouds; mostly clear sky.
See comments for site #663150 for this date.
Submitted comments is for this site and #663045.  Sky is 80% overcast with negligible wind.  Air temp 77 degrees.  Water clarity is continuing to improve with minimal pollen suspended in the water.
Negligible wind- calm surface- 5% cloud cover- air temperatue at 86 degrees.  This data is applicable to site #663150 on same lake for readings on this date.

High cirrus clouds- air temp at 85 degrees- wind from the south at approximately 15 mph.  Light wave action.  Considerable boat traffic on the lake this Labor Day weekend.  Lake appears to have turned over- as water clarity is nearly half of what had been observed two week earlier.

column1: Above comments apply to both sites on Balsam Lake.

column1: Wind from the south at approximately 10 knots; light wave action; air temperature approximately 70 degrees.  Less than 10% cloud cover.
This is the final submission of data for Balsam Lake sites #663045 and #663150 for 2008.

column2: Same information applies as enter for site #663150.

Mostly clear sky with light wind from west and minimal wave action.  Air temp is 81 degrees.  Water quality (appearance) is markedly less than two weeks earlier- with fair amount of suspended pollen particles in the water.

Clear sky with less than 5% clouds; air temp at 86 degrees with light breeze from northwest and minimal wave action.  Significant improvement in water quality observed since previous readings two and four weeks ago.  The lake has lost its only eagle nest on the east shore (immediately east of public boat landing) apparently from heavy winds in late winter/early spring.  This nest was established back in the early 1980's.  No newly-built nest is visible along lake's shortline.  Fewer number of eagles- two or less- have been sighted in past month.  There is a significant reduction in the number of squirrels (gray- black + red) on our east shore property- however this has been offset by a doubling of the number of chipmunks from last year.  Several neighbors reporting similar observations.
No wind; dead calm.  High cirrus clouds with air temp in mid-70's.  One of only two boats on the lake.  Sun angle still high enough for an adequate reading.
See entered data for site #663150 on Balsam Lake on this date.
Same information as entered for site #663150 same lake- same date.

Along with data submitted on this date for site # 663150- a significant change in water clarity has been noted for both sites on Balsam Lake.  Appears to be increased levels of botom sediment suspended in the water.
